Nepal government organized the first South-South conference on World Dalit Solidarity to highlight the network of relations between South-South countries celebrating the Decade of 20 Year of Social Parliamentary Action on People and Plinths. The South-South Conference on World Dalit Solidarity was organized from the 8th to 11th October 2013 in the World Conference Center Borden in Bhutan. Around 1200 leaders of various well-known organizations of different parts of the world to share and exchange successful experiences and initiate to find joint solutions for the global pandemic of the 21st century for the one and a single society.
